<!--
  TWILIO CONFERENCE JOIN TwiML
  ============================

  WHAT THIS IS:
  This is the TwiML that runs when Line's `transfer_call` dials the
  CONFERENCE_JOIN_NUMBER. It drops the caller into the shared conference
  room where Taylor or Aryamaan are already waiting (they were placed
  there by the outbound probe call — see escalation.py).

  HOW THE FLOW WORKS (for context):
    1. Bot decides to escalate.
    2. escalation.py places outbound probe calls to Taylor and Aryamaan
       with inline TwiML that drops them into conference "bc-active".
    3. If either answers, they're now in the conference.
    4. Line's transfer_call is called with CONFERENCE_JOIN_NUMBER.
    5. Twilio dials CONFERENCE_JOIN_NUMBER, which runs this TwiML.
    6. The caller joins the same conference room. Everyone is bridged.

  HOW TO SET UP:
    1. Buy a second Twilio number (the "conference join" number).
    2. Create a TwiML Bin (Twilio Console → Runtime → TwiML Bins).
    3. Paste the <Response>...</Response> block below. Change the
       conference name ONLY if you also changed CONFERENCE_NAME in .env
       (default is "bc-active").
    4. Copy the TwiML Bin's URL.
    5. Configure the second Twilio number's Voice webhook to point at
       the TwiML Bin URL.
    6. Set CONFERENCE_JOIN_NUMBER in .env to that second number.

  You do NOT need a separate TwiML Bin for the outbound probe — that
  TwiML is built inline in escalation.py and passed via the Twilio
  calls.create(twiml=...) parameter.
-->

<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8"?>
<Response>
  <Dial>
    <Conference
      startConferenceOnEnter="true"
      endConferenceOnExit="true"
      beep="false"
    >bc-active</Conference>
  </Dial>
</Response>
